.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::Repost \- NIP\-18 reposts and generic reposts
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use Net::Nostr::Repost;
\&
\&    # Repost a kind 1 text note (creates kind 6)
\&    my $repost = Net::Nostr::Repost\->repost(
\&        event     => $note,
\&        pubkey    => $my_pubkey,
\&        relay_url => \*(Aqwss://relay.example.com\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Repost any other event (creates kind 16)
\&    my $repost = Net::Nostr::Repost\->repost(
\&        event     => $article,
\&        pubkey    => $my_pubkey,
\&        relay_url => \*(Aqwss://relay.example.com\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Quote repost (adds q tag)
\&    my $repost = Net::Nostr::Repost\->repost(
\&        event     => $note,
\&        pubkey    => $my_pubkey,
\&        relay_url => \*(Aqwss://relay.example.com\*(Aq,
\&        quote     => 1,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Parse repost structure from an event
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::Repost\->from_event($event);
\&    if ($info) {
\&        say "Reposted event: " . $info\->event_id;
\&        say "From relay: " . $info\->relay_url;
\&        if ($info\->embedded_event) {
\&            say "Content: " . $info\->embedded_event\->content;
\&        }
\&    }
\&
\&    # Validate a repost event
\&    Net::Nostr::Repost\->validate($event);
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-18 reposts. A repost is a kind 6 event for sharing kind 1
text notes, or a kind 16 "generic repost" for sharing any other event kind.
.PP
The repost content is the stringified JSON of the reposted event (MAY be
empty). Reposts of NIP\-70 <https://github.com/nostr-protocol/nips/blob/master/70.md>\-protected
events SHOULD always have an empty content. Tags include an \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag with
the event ID and relay URL (MUST), a \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tag with the original author
(SHOULD), and for generic reposts a \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag with the stringified kind
(SHOULD) and an \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag with the event coordinate for addressable events
(SHOULD).
.PP
Quote reposts use a \f(CW\*(C`q\*(C'\fR tag instead of being pulled into reply threads.
The \f(CW\*(C`q\*(C'\fR tag format is
\&\f(CW\*(C`["q", "<event\-id>", "<relay\-url>", "<pubkey>"]\*(C'\fR.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new
.IX Subsection "new"
.Vb 1
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::Repost\->new(%fields);
.Ve
.PP
Creates a new \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Repost\*(C'\fR object.  Typically returned by
"from_event"; calling \f(CW\*(C`new\*(C'\fR directly is useful for testing or
manual construction.
.PP
.Vb 4
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::Repost\->new(
\&        event_id    => \*(Aqaa\*(Aq x 32,
\&        relay_url   => \*(Aqwss://relay.example.com\*(Aq,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Accepted fields: \f(CW\*(C`event_id\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`relay_url\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`author_pubkey\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`reposted_kind\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`event_coordinate\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`embedded_event\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`quote_event_id\*(C'\fR. Croaks on unknown arguments.
.SH "CLASS METHODS"
.IX Header "CLASS METHODS"
.SS repost
.IX Subsection "repost"
.Vb 8
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Repost\->repost(
\&        event      => $original_event,    # Net::Nostr::Event to repost
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,        # reposter\*(Aqs hex pubkey
\&        relay_url  => \*(Aqwss://relay.example.com\*(Aq,
\&        content    => \*(Aq\*(Aq,                 # optional, override content
\&        quote      => 1,                  # optional, add q tag
\&        created_at => time(),             # optional, passed to Event
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a repost Net::Nostr::Event. If the original event is kind 1,
creates a kind 6 repost. Otherwise creates a kind 16 generic repost with
a \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag and (for addressable events) an \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag.
.PP
The \f(CW\*(C`event\*(C'\fR parameter is the Net::Nostr::Event being reposted. The
\&\f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR is the reposter\*(Aqs hex public key (the original author\*(Aqs pubkey
is taken from the event\*(Aqs \f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR field for the \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tag).
.PP
The content defaults to the stringified JSON of the original event. Pass
\&\f(CW\*(C`content => \*(Aq\*(Aq\*(C'\fR to create a repost with empty content (e.g. for
NIP\-70 <https://github.com/nostr-protocol/nips/blob/master/70.md>\-protected
events).
.PP
Pass \f(CW\*(C`quote => 1\*(C'\fR to add a \f(CW\*(C`q\*(C'\fR tag for quote reposts.
.PP
Returns a Net::Nostr::Event with the appropriate kind, tags, and content.
.PP
Croaks if \f(CW\*(C`event\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR, or \f(CW\*(C`relay_url\*(C'\fR is missing.
.SS from_event
.IX Subsection "from_event"
.Vb 1
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::Repost\->from_event($event);
.Ve
.PP
Parses repost structure from a kind 6 or kind 16 Net::Nostr::Event.
Returns a \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Repost\*(C'\fR object with accessors, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if
the event is not a repost kind.
.PP
.Vb 3
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::Repost\->from_event($event);
\&    say $info\->event_id;                         # reposted event id
\&    say $info\->embedded_event\->content if $info\->embedded_event;
.Ve
.SS validate
.IX Subsection "validate"
.Vb 1
\&    Net::Nostr::Repost\->validate($event);
.Ve
.PP
Validates that a Net::Nostr::Event is a well\-formed NIP\-18 repost.
Croaks if:
.IP \(bu 4
Kind is not 6 or 16
.IP \(bu 4
Missing \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag missing relay URL
.PP
.Vb 2
\&    eval { Net::Nostr::Repost\->validate($event) };
\&    warn "Invalid repost: $@" if $@;
.Ve
.SH ACCESSORS
.IX Header "ACCESSORS"
These are available on objects returned by "from_event".
.SS event_id
.IX Subsection "event_id"
.Vb 1
\&    my $id = $info\->event_id;
.Ve
.PP
The ID of the reposted event (from the \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag).
.SS relay_url
.IX Subsection "relay_url"
.Vb 1
\&    my $url = $info\->relay_url;
.Ve
.PP
The relay URL where the reposted event can be fetched (from the \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag).
.SS author_pubkey
.IX Subsection "author_pubkey"
.Vb 1
\&    my $pk = $info\->author_pubkey;
.Ve
.PP
The pubkey of the original event author (from the \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tag), or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR.
.SS reposted_kind
.IX Subsection "reposted_kind"
.Vb 1
\&    my $kind = $info\->reposted_kind;  # \*(Aq30023\*(Aq
.Ve
.PP
The stringified kind of the reposted event (from the \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag), or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR.
Only present on kind 16 generic reposts.
.SS event_coordinate
.IX Subsection "event_coordinate"
.Vb 1
\&    my $coord = $info\->event_coordinate;  # \*(Aq30023:pubkey:d\-tag\*(Aq
.Ve
.PP
The event coordinate (from the \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag), or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR. Only present when
reposting addressable events.
.SS embedded_event
.IX Subsection "embedded_event"
.Vb 1
\&    my $event = $info\->embedded_event;  # Net::Nostr::Event or undef
.Ve
.PP
The reposted event parsed from the repost\*(Aqs content field. Returns \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR
if the content is empty or cannot be parsed as a valid event.
.SS quote_event_id
.IX Subsection "quote_event_id"
.Vb 1
\&    my $qid = $info\->quote_event_id;  # event id or undef
.Ve
.PP
The quoted event ID (from the \f(CW\*(C`q\*(C'\fR tag), or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR. Present only when
the repost is a quote repost.
